# Testes Unitários — Jest

## 0) Princípios
- **Unit tests** obrigatórios em: use-cases, domain, funções de use-case do frontend.
- **Integration tests** quando necessário: repositórios TypeORM (banco real ou testcontainers).
- Sem testes de timing de fila.
- Arquivo de teste co-localizado: `create-lead.use-case.spec.ts` ao lado de `create-lead.use-case.ts`.

---

## 1) Use-case (packages/use-cases)
```ts
// packages/use-cases/src/leads/__tests__/create-lead.use-case.spec.ts
import { CreateLeadUseCase } from '../create-lead.use-case'
import { BusinessRuleViolation } from '@repo/domain'

// Mock tipado da interface de repositório
const makeLeadRepo = (): jest.Mocked<ILeadRepository> => ({
  findByEmail: jest.fn(),
  save: jest.fn(),
  getByIdOrFail: jest.fn(),
  listWithFilters: jest.fn(),
})

describe('CreateLeadUseCase', () => {
  let useCase: CreateLeadUseCase
  let leadRepo: jest.Mocked<ILeadRepository>

  beforeEach(() => {
    leadRepo = makeLeadRepo()
    useCase = new CreateLeadUseCase(leadRepo)
  })

  it('cria lead com sucesso quando email não existe', async () => {
    leadRepo.findByEmail.mockResolvedValue(null)
    leadRepo.save.mockResolvedValue({ id: 'uuid-1', name: 'João', email: 'joao@ex.com' } as any)

    const result = await useCase.execute({ name: 'João', email: 'joao@ex.com' })

    expect(result.id).toBe('uuid-1')
    expect(leadRepo.findByEmail).toHaveBeenCalledWith('joao@ex.com')
    expect(leadRepo.save).toHaveBeenCalledOnce()
  })

  it('lança BusinessRuleViolation quando email já existe', async () => {
    leadRepo.findByEmail.mockResolvedValue({ id: 'uuid-1' } as any)

    await expect(useCase.execute({ name: 'João', email: 'joao@ex.com' }))
      .rejects.toThrow(BusinessRuleViolation)

    expect(leadRepo.save).not.toHaveBeenCalled()
  })
})
```

